PK "PLAYER KILLING" PLAYER KILLING

While this help file is far from complete, the basic out-lines are listed.
More rules and regulations will be added so continue to check this file.
Remember, these rules are laid out to help avoid conflict and make pk'ing
fair to everyone.

If you don't like them, quit and re-start your character without pk.

1) Pk'ing starts at level 30. No pk'ing is allowed below that. If you do
   you will receive a "Killer" flag and any mob or player is allowed to
   kill you.

2) Pk levels are 7 levels within your own. That mean 7 up, 7 down. No more
   with level 30's starting at level 30 - 37.

3) No spam pk'ing. You MUST wait a minimum of 15 - 20 minutes before
   pk'ing the same player. While we have left this up to your discretion,
   it can be checked to make sure you're following the rules.

4) Since you are allowed to have at max  2 characters on the mud, and this
   ties in with clans, all your chars MUST be in the same clan or no clan
   at all. This goes for strictly pk clans if any are on the mud or any
   are started. So if you have one pk char and one not but are already in
   a clan, your other char has the option of joining that clan (depends
   soully on the clan leader) or not joining any clan.

5) No using "summon", "teleport", "portal" whatever for pk'ing. You have
   two feet, use them.

6) You are ONLY allowed to kill other pk players that have the flag.

7) Once you choose pk you are stuck with it unless you delete your
   character and restart over. You will NOT be advanced to your previous
   level.

8) No jumping in on a pk fight, period. Unless ALL parties agree to it. In
   other words, no gang pk'ing.

9) No disarming or stealing/taking eq while pk'ing. Using spells is
   perfectly legal.

10) No going afk or doing anything else to avoid pk'ing. You've decided to
    pk so if you didn't want to pk you shouldn't have chosen it. No one
    has to warn you before they kill you and no one has to ask your
    permission. Once you have that flag you are fair game to other pk'ers
    around your level. So no hard feelings against other pk players since
    you didn't have to choose pk. Going afk and saying you were busy is
    not an excuse, quit if you're going to be busy.

11) No hiding in houses to avoid pk'ing or juicing yourself up with
    spells. A God or Imp has the right to move you out of your house if
    they feel you are hiding in there to avoid being killed. Plus if it's
    continually done an Imp has the right to kill you themselves to teach 
    you a lesson for hiding. So you are now warned ahead of time.

Thats about it folks!

