HERO PRINCE KNIGHT

Once you reach level 100 here on minos you deserve some kind of reward, so
the mighty Zeus went and put his thinking hat on and came up with the idea
of heros.

Therefore when you reach this level you get hero status. Now you may think
that this is good enough in its own right, you can wander round the world
of minos going 'Look everybody I'm a Hero!' boosting your ever inflated
ego.

Well not only can you do that but well you can cast any spell or use any
skill you like. 

Being the kind god that Zeus is he thought well those hero types might
not have enough practice sessions to learn all those wounderfull new
spells and skills.

So he added a nice new commands called HERO which allows you to get more
practice sessions, well it didn't stop there the commands also lets you
max all your stats out too...

... Now before you go running round the room with a big grin, while
shouting some strange Mud babble which well other people in the room might
not understand and if you think about it they might call a doctor!

Anyway all this maxing of stats and getting practices comes at a small
cost, your experience points, now depending on what you do each thing
costs a different amount so for a list just type the command on its own
and it will tell you what to do.

Depending on your heroicness you can exchange those experience points for
more things... the higher the level the more you get, thats because as you
become a better hero you can do more things.

So if your already a hero then well done otherwise keep at it and you'll
soon become one.

Note on the Hero command:

Hero command changes your stats as they would be with no eq on. It then
re-applies the eq modifiers. It is best to remove all eq when applying
this command on stats so that you get a true picture of how your stats
are being increased. For example if you had a wisdom of 12 and used the
hero command to increase it then it would go up by one. If however you had
some eq which did +6 wisdom, then the score command would show your wis as
18, however your real wisdom is still only 12, and so the hero command can
be used to increase that stat further. In other words the hero command
increases REAL stats not modified ones.

